==English==

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-dot.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# A small spot.
#:''a '''dot''' of colour''
# A symbol marking the end of a sentence (a [[full stop]] or [[period]]).
# A symbol replacing the part of a word or words removed to form an [[abbreviation]].
# {{mathematics}} A symbol separating the [[decimal part]] of a [[decimal]] from the [[whole part]], indicating [[multiplication]], a [[scalar product]], or in various other meanings.
# One of the two symbols used in [[Morse code]].

====Synonyms====
*(''small spot''): [[speck]], [[spot]]
*(''at the end of a sentence''): {{UK}} [[full stop]], {{UK}} [[period]]
*(''in an abbreviation''): [[point]]
*(''mathematics''): (''in a decimal'') [[decimal point]]
*(''in Morse code''): [[dit]]

